title: Chicago  -- Night and Day -- XXIII (23)
description:
Big bands came back into style for about 10 seconds in the 1990s and Chicago was there.  These tracks are really pretty good, especially the title track and "Goody Goody."  These guys are talented.  Believe it.


This album contains:


Chicago

Caravan

Dream a LIttle Dream of Me

Goody Goody

Moonlight Serenade

Night & Day

Blues in the Night

Sing, Sing, Sing

Sophisticated Lady

In the Mood

Don&#039;t Get Around Much Anymore

Take the "A" Train


CHICAGO BELONGS IN THE HALL OF FAME!  DELIVER THEM THERE!!!
